How to Install Nmap on Manjaro
Step 1: Update Package Database

Open your terminal and run:

sudo pacman -Syu


This updates your package list and upgrades existing packages.

Step 2: Install Nmap

Run the following command to install Nmap:

sudo pacman -S nmap

Step 3: Verify Installation

Check if Nmap is installed correctly by typing:

nmap --version


You should see the version info of Nmap printed.

Step 4: Run a Simple Scan (Optional)

Try scanning your localhost:

nmap 127.0.0.1


This will scan ports on your local machine.

Done! You now have Nmap installed and ready to use on Manjaro.
